Events.Title: Costume "Shop
Events.Description: Be inspired to create a costume or character from our racks. What Bedtime Story will you tell?

Events.Title: dcbbq :: Delicious BBQ & Community Smoker
Events.Description:
dcbbq has a dedicated smoker for use by the LoF community.  Basic orientation is required; swing by camp and find an authorized dcbbq agent. Rules: We will not babysit your food, and we will not accept donations of unwanted meat/food.  Radical self-reliance, y'all!

dcbbq will curate, smoke, and gift hundreds of pounds of our own delicious BBQ during LoF.  Look for the "Meat Wagon" cruising around the event, servin' up smokey morsels. Rules: The BBQ is ready when it's ready, and always wait to be served.


Every day

Events.Title: All Day Mini Golf
Events.Location: Great Lakes Miniature Municipal Country Club
Events.Description: Come bask in the good life at the Great Lakes Miniature Municipal Country Club and play our three hole mini golf course. Explore the Magical Garden Hole, the Egyptian Hole,  and the Seaside Hole. Come waste a good walk and hit the links.
Events.HumanLocation: Great Lakes Miniature Municipal Country Club  | Site K6

Events.Title: Anahata ~ The Temple That Love Built
Events.Description: Anahata ~ Sanskrit for "unhurt, unstruck, and unbeaten" ~ is that place in our story where we make meaning. Beyond our hurt and grievances is space for processing, forgiving, keeping healthy boundaries, and integrating what we�ve learned. Let�s meet there! Anahata: The Temple That Love Built is a haven filled with Heart-centered art, interactive experiences, and workshops to foster spirits of joy, love, compassion, acceptance, forgiveness, and personal peace. Join us daily for sunrise/sunset yoga and check the WWW or the schedule outside the temple for specific workshop and performance times. Events are subject to change.

Events.Title: Axe Throwing of the Gods
Events.Description: It's like darts, but with axes. Supervised by a Valhalla Viking. Times may vary

Events.Title: Bedtime Stories Library and Lounge
Events.Description: Enjoy our 9ft round sultan style lounge where you can relax and enjoy selections from our Bedtime Storybook Library.

Events.Title: Beer O'Clock
Events.Description: Keep an eye out for the sign at the Thirsty Sphinx Bar! When the planets align and a Sphinx bartender emerges from the cosmos, the sign will go up at our bar and the sweet brewed nectar will flow! Bring your cup to share in the Sphinx�s liquid bounty - non-alcoholic beverages will also be offered.

Events.Title: Board Games
Events.Description: If you see the board games out pop a squat, and have some fun. Sorry, there may be times when the games are not available. Fuck yer day!

Events.Title: Brand New Buddy ...Bench?
Events.Description:
A place to find a new buddy! Be the first to offer yourself to the brand new buddy gods, or be the one who completes the brand new buddy pair (or triad! Or.. whatever). 

New this year is a fancy umbrella and Cards to the Heart (Cards created by our very own LoF family member Dom!)

Events.Title: Capture the Flag- Flag Decoration
Events.Description: Come by Valhalla! and get your blank canvas flag, art it up, and show your theme camp pride! Coincides with Opt- In Theme Camp Capture the Flag on Friday

Events.Title: Frozen Kraken Creamery
Events.Description: Once again Frozen Kraken Creamery will be back at Lucky Lake to serve creamy goodness down the throat holes of all it's denizens. Check out our new Superman ice cream now made with even more dolphin bits.

Events.Title: Gaming with the Sphinxters
Events.Description: Stop in any time to join a table or yard game of your choice. Table games will be under the tent and yard games by the bar; come while away an hour in play!

Events.Title: Guacamole
Events.Description: All that you can imagine and much much more... Electronica provided by Don Pedro from Dolbos Stereo. Fuego and incendios provided by Don Juan�to aka El Propane Sideshow. Funk and bass brought to you by Santo Uno from the mountain city of Auto Reverso. Whiskey�s provided by el jefe de pachangas grandes, Nick Del Amor�.

Events.Title: Hammerschlaggen
Events.Description: A tradition and a favorite.  Toss a hammer, catch it, hit the nail.  Sounds easy right?

Events.Title: Happiness hours
Events.Description: Lux Ephemera welcomes you to join us for  libations, (yeah! We have a bar now!) Crafted with home made simple syrups infused with all sorts of lovely botanicals!  Hang out in our lovingly assembled chillspace and groove along to what our dj is spinning... you'll never guess what he's playing!

Events.Title: Jingles Emporium
Events.Description: Jingles Emporium provides those sometimes hard-to-find necessary items items like: Cigarettes, Lighters, Water, Tampax, Toilet Paper, and more!  Open 24 hours, self serve, stop by the baby trailer at Pleasure House.

Events.Title: Lakes of Fire Pronoun Project
Events.Description:
Lakes of Fire is dedicated to taking a more inclusive stance by acknowledging gender diversity at our event. By allowing individuals to represent themselves with their preferred pronouns, we can establish authentic and personal connections right from the start. 

Stop by the Greeter's station anytime while gate is open and pick up a pronoun button. You will be able to write your preferred pronouns on the button and wear it throughout the event. We encourage all gender identities to participate in order to provide an inclusive environment for everyone.

Events.Title: Looking Glass Lounge
Events.Location: Camp Natural Wonderland - Looking Glass Lounge
Events.Description: Origami, coloring books, interactive art, henna, and more! Come by the Looking Glass Lounge and get creative with us.
Events.HumanLocation: Camp Natural Wonderland - Looking Glass Lounge | Site 18

Events.Title: Lounge of the Gods
Events.Description: The Lounge has expanded with more space to recline and rest your weary warrior bones upon the lush fur-covered inflatable.  Vikings will tell the tales of the heroes and gods of days gone by while you sip mugs of glogg, and prepare for Ragnarok by sharpening your skills at hammerschlagen.

Events.Title: Meet the Genies of the InGenieous Lamp
Events.Description: InGenieous, the giant Genie Lamp, welcomes participants to come meet the Genies and Jinn of the lamp everyday!  Each day the Genies will open their lamp up to those who dare to enter and behold the magic within.  What you find is up to you! What will you wish for?  The lamp will be open spontaneously, but frequently, please come back if the Genies are not in when you stop by.

Events.Title: Monkeys, Monkeys, Bananas & Monkeys
Events.Description: You get a Monkey & You get a Monkey & You get a Banana

Events.Title: Mysterious Locked Chest Year 3
Events.Description:
By now you know the drill... Follow the clues... Open the Mysterious Locked Chest (tm)... Win the prize inside.

Did you figure out where it is hidden? Did you realize there is a clue in this WWW guide listing? Did you bring your amethyst crystal?

You have until Exodus day at 11:57AM

Events.Title: Oracle of the Sphinx
Events.Description: Come lounge, explore, and discover the secrets of our large lady! This LoF art grant piece  is an interactive physical riddle in a form you�re sure to recognize. If you beguile her appropriately, she might even allow you to depart with a few words of wisdom, or a glimpse into your future...

Events.Title: Pie Hole
Events.Description: We never shut our pie hole, it's open 24/7. Cuddle puddle in pizza painted yurt.
Events.HumanLocation: Cat Mom's Pizza Club | Site K20

Events.Title: Private Memorial Space
Events.Description: Do you have a loved one you want to honor, but would like to do it in a less public way? Stop by the Honorarium and use the space to memorialize the deceased in your own private way. No grand speeches necessary. There will be daily public memorial services from 10:00 A.M to 11:30 A.M for those who want to share their tributes with an audience.

Events.Title: Regret, Relive, and Release
Events.Description: Is there something in your life that you wish could have went down differently? Maybe you would have liked to experience something with a loved one, but that person is now deceased. Possibly a bonding trip with an estranged sibling, your long-departed father getting to meet his grandchild, or an experience of baking cookies with a grandma you never knew. Use this opportunity to write a new narrative about an experience, and your relationship with the people who are no longer in your life. Take a regret, relive it in a new way, and release the pain.

Events.Title: Scavenger Hunt
Events.Description: Let's have a scavenger hunt!  Stop by Camp Drink Bitch & get your list of items for which to be on the lookout.  Lists will be available in a self service container (look for sign). Bring your completed hunt back to our Camp by Sat morning, during posted activity times,  for a fun little reward!

Events.Title: Sphinx's Menagerie
Events.Description: Come borrow a trusty steed from our floaty corral to aid you on your lake-bound adventures! We�ll be offering all manner of beasties for your buoyancy assistance needs. We do ask that you kindly return your creature to its paddock for the night when you�ve finished your aquatic cavorting.

Events.Title: Take a Book, Leave a Book
Events.Description: Browse the books of the Lucky Lake Burner Library and choose a textual friend to take home and cuddle. (We do mean books!) Or, chat with a librarian, get a book recommendation, or take a stern shushin' for the road.
Events.HumanLocation: Lucky Lake Burner Library | Site K4

Events.Title: The Exquisite Corpse
Events.Description: The Exquisite Corpse is a surreal collaborative writing experiment. Come visit Iris, our very own Exquisite Corpse, participate in the experiment, and help our communal story grow. Iris will reveal only the most recent lines of the story before you add something of your own. The result will be a bizarre, phantasmagorical Bedtime Story created by the collective imagination of the Lucky Lake community. We will edit the resulting work and share it with the Lakes of Fire Facebook group.
Events.HumanLocation: Lucky Lake Burner Library | Site K4

Events.Title: The Ravishing Rose Suite
Events.Description: Hospitality. Luxury. A retreat from the oontz-oontz. Air Burn~n~Burn aims to offer two Lucky Lake citizens a stay in our Ravishing Rose Suite each night. Winners will be chosen by drawing and are invited at dusk for a turndown service and a stay in our luxury suite surrounded by roses and fairy lights in a bedroom all their own. Upon their waking, they will be treated to breakfast. Leave feeling pampered and renewed, or at least well rested and well fed. After housekeeping changes the linens and restores cleanliness, the room will be open for another night.

Events.Title: Windsurfing
Events.Description: Come by camp Chemical Lemonade any time the wind is blowing to get a windsurfing lesson or to borrow a windsurfer.

Events.Title: You Are the Star at Susan
Events.Description: This year, Gothee House and Moofi have joined forces, and in addition to the Caf� and Habitat, we have a stage!  When the stage isn't being used for other performances, stop by and take the stage yourself!  Or hang out in the cafe and perform if you don't want to be as formal.  Play music, sing, recite bedtime stories, do a poetry slam!  Perform magic, mime, act like a statue, do stand up comedy!  Pretty much any kind of performance is fine as long as it upholds the standards of respect for which the burner community is known.

Events.Title: Binary 10s AM Digeridoo Sounding
Events.Description:
Dreamtime is over, the day begins anew.  Around The Lake are ~10 digeridoos.  With one of these or your own, Join in our Communal Drone..!
(& After Sunday @ 10:10AM, take a didge home with you...)

Events.Title: Open Bar
Events.Description: Stop by the Consortium for a full service bar.  Each day will feature a specialty handcrafted cocktail masterminded by a bartender. If you like craft beer, the Consortium is the place to be!  9 different beers and 3 ciders were specifically made for your enjoyment.

Events.Title: Basic Bike Repair Workshop
Events.Description: Learn how to do basic repairs, adjusting brakes, changing tires, and some easy preventive maintnence on your wheeled steed, or someone elses! Hosted by Lolo
Events.HumanLocation: Camp Bikes and Brew | Site K19

Events.Title: Capn Nemo's Flaming Carnival
Events.Description: Join the fun daily at Capn Nemo's Flaming Carnival, and remember to come back Friday night for our famous (infamous) Dance Party!

Events.Title: Gothee House Coffee
Events.Description: Come to the Gothee House cafe at Susan for good company and fresh hot coffee, dark like our souls. Coffee is served from early afternoon through the witching hour.  The cafe is located in the Susan courtyard with a good view of the stage.  As always, visitors are advised against signing contracts with magical creatures or following ghostly women into the woods.  Oh wait, why are we advising against that?  Please do so and then we can tell bedtime stories about you.

Events.Title: Mystical Mike's Tarot and Tequila
Events.Description:
The Tarot is a wonderful tool of self examination.  Tequila is a wonderful tool of self examination.  Anything more effective is likely to be illegal or way expensive.   Mystical Mike will stand you to a shot of top shelf tequila, read your cards and provide a  hanky or hug, as needed. 
Tequila is optional, so ACCOMPANIED minors are welcome.
(Green Dragon Lounge is not kid proofed.)

Events.Title: Personal Obituary Writing Workshop
Events.Description: How would you feel about your story if it ended today? Have you accomplished all that you wanted to? Do you feel good about the legacy you would be leaving behind?   By envisioning our death in an immediate way, we create space to live our lives more fully. Let�s discuss how to put pen to paper on a topic that can be jarring.  Bring a reflective mind and your imagination.

Events.Title: (+/-) Lemonade Social
Events.Description: Hot and tired from setting up your camp? Don't have the forearm strength to open up your own drink? Fear not, the women of Drink, Bitch will do it for you. Come chill, shine (or rain) with us for some choice insults, compliments, possible bizarreness, and for a cold sumthin' sumthin' and some Scooby snacks. May contain caffeine and/or alcohol and carbohydrates. Bring yo' cup, and remember to lick your fingers when done.

Events.Title: Snickerin' Tick Tavern
Events.Description: Come spin the Ticker Twirl and enjoy our libations!

Events.Title: Spanks & Dranks
Events.Description: Spanks & Dranks is a fun, interactive bar run by Pleasure House. Creative drinks are served and even more creative spankings are administered.  Maybe you will end up in the stocks or paddled with our assorted instruments of pleasure and pain.  You don't have to get spanked to get a drank but it's more fun if you do!

Events.Title: Mutant Kazoo Adoption Hour
Events.Description: Squeaky Toot's Musical Menagerie has been overrun by a slew of Mutant Kazoos! For today only, we are waiving all adoption fee!. All that is required is a small spot of paperwork and a brief instrument parenting competency interview. And then (pending your results) your lifelong bond with one of our mutated little squeakers can begin! (*The Closet Fort Kingdom waives all liability from injuries sustained from annoyed neighbors)
Events.HumanLocation: The Closet Fort Kingdom | Site K2

Events.Title: Substance checking, Harm Reduction Info and Supplies
Events.Description: Serves as an Info Booth for drugs/Harm reduction, and offers info/earplugs/SafeSexSupplies/straws/water, as well as offers drug reagent-testing

Events.Title: Lakes of Fire Newbie Orientation
Events.Description: First time at Lakes of Fire? First Burn of any kind? Do you have questions about the event or the Burning Man community in general? Well then, stop by the Greeter's station Wednesday, Thursday or Friday at 6:15 p.m. All your questions will be answered. There might even be some sweet swag for inquiring newbies.

Events.Title: Massage Party
Events.Description: Come on down to The Pleasure House for some Lakes of Fire legendary Multi Handed Massage at our Pleasure House.  Let the stress of Lakes of Fire melt away with the Famous Multi Handed Massage. This event is "Consent ONLY ". This will take place on Wednesday Evening June 13th Starting about 6pm to 8pm.

Events.Title: Ancient Gods: Myth and Mingle
Events.Description: Kick off your Lakes celebration at the Thirsty Sphinx Bar! Come check out our camp offerings, sip some sphinxy brew, and partake in a round or two of themed bar trivia with Sphinxter Darek! Costumes encouraged! Dress as your favorite deity or your fanciest toga and come ready to get down. The gods were the first bedtime stories after all.

Events.Title: Dance Party & Shenanigans
Events.Description: Tortuga will be up all night every night drinking, partying, and paddlin' asses. Featuring: Booze, Pirates, and two DJ's scratchin' that "Get Drunk and Dance" itch. Stop by, get yourself a drink from the Boozey Bar�nacle, take a load off in the Merry Marauder's Lounge, and  dance until your wooden leg falls off.

Events.Title: Firewater Lounge Welcome Party
Events.Description:
All the folks who have been setting up camps, building the effigy or volunteer for critical teams need a place to go the first night they can party.  Let's be that place!!  Open the bar, music and bar snacks!

7 pm setup; 8 - 10 event; 10 cleanup

Events.Title: Jam Band Dance Party and Grilled Cheese Sandwich Bar
Events.Description:
Where do the hippies go when they get off your lawn?  A Jam Band Dance Party at a Grilled Cheese Sandwich Bar, naturally.
Neolithic Hippie Burners and those who love them are invited to shake their bones to the Grateful Dead, Phish and other faves, while authentic hippies grill you a fresh hot  cheese sandwich on the spot, with your choice of traditional and eclectic toppings.   
Shoes optional.

Events.Title: The Doktor is In? (open hours dictated by ongoing medical emergencies)
Events.Description:
Look for "The Doktor Is In" sign. (Hey! Sometimes we gotta work!)
Stop in at the Pharmacy & Schott Klinik (hosted by the ESD Volunteers) for some kinda beverage.
Unapproved (and uncomfortable) medical procedures & examinations will be available on demand.
Medically necessary corporal punishment will be offered and administered by our "Pleasure Dept" (administered by trained professionals) We put the F-U in fun!
**expectations of niceness, correctness, understanding or sympathy will be completely ignored**

Events.Title: TomatoTim Bday bash
Events.Description: Wednesday night will be a night to remember.. WE will be celebrating the b-day of our amazing Effigy Co-lead TomatoTim!  Come and help us celebrate! It will be a chill gathering - some snacks, some drinks, some cake...  don't miss it!

Events.Title: BANG  Bedtime Stories
Events.Description: Bring your blankies and jammies to BANG for a  reading of a specially curated adult bedtime story. Some are frightening and a few are just hot. Come help us set the tone for the night.

Events.Title: Revs Flame Thrower Nachos and Tree of Za Oven Baked Pizza
Events.Description:
At dusk every night, stop by the Consortium for Tree of Za Oven Baked Pizzas and Revs Flame Thrower Nachos.  Hand tossed pizza dough and fresh ingredients will rock your socks.

If you havent had Revs Flame Thrower Nachos yet, youre in for a treat.

Events.Title: Kraken Floats
Events.Description: Once again, Frozen Kraken Kreamery is taking over the Syncytium Bar to sling cream down unsuspecting throats. Come join us for Root Beer Floats - alcoholic and otherwise - to kick the first night of the burn off right.

Events.Title: Partnered and Couple ONLY" Play Party
Events.Description: Join us at The Pleasure House as we will host a party for our Awesome Couples at Lakes of Fire.  Will be having one of our AWESOME Play parties that is all inclusive catering to "PARTNERS and COUPLES ONLY".  We will be starting about 8PM to 12AM on Wednesday June 13th.  There will be lots of "Consent ONLY Play" and New Equipment to use, on us ! !  Start your Lakes of Fire the right way ! ! !

Events.Title: Where are all the Pickles?
Events.Description:
The phase is opening... The phase... is opening... We will have food, punk music (tonight only), and drinks, of course! 

Also wtf is a Pickle Back?

Events.Title: Bedtime Snacktime
Events.Description:
Sweet dreams with whipped cream and a cookie!
 
Want a bedtime snack? Come find us every night on our rounds around Lucky Lake- we'll be serving cookie sundaes!

Events.Description: Come help Doktor Dragon open up the Green Dragon Lounge

Events.Description: A Safe, Comfortable space for people having a difficult mental experience (due to any reason)

Events.Title: Worst First Dates
Events.Description: Look back and laugh as we explore some of our most disastrous but memorable first dates.  Share your tinder tragedy or blind date bumble and even your not missed connections with fellow story tellers.

Events.Title: Martinis and Mancini
Events.Description:
The Pleasure House presents an evening of urbane relaxation featuring the music of Henry Mancini.  Revisit a simpler time before the internet and EDM and enjoy a martini or two.  

Come experience a chill event.

Events.Description: Do you have a scary or interesting story that others might not know?  Maybe something passed down through your family or discovered in some obscure text?  Come share this story with your fellow storytellers!

Events.Title: Clayton the Whale
Events.Description: Stop by Camp Burnlesque to paint Clayton the Whale, a gentle giant made out of sheet metal. This sassy sperm whale can't seem to keep his skin on, so we need you to paint it on! He loves being interacted with so come by anytime the sun is out, and members of our camp can give you the tools needed to paint and create!

Events.Location: Burning Belgian Beer in Camp Not Sure
Events.Description: Fire, for the passionate;  Earth, for the stable;  Air, for the care-free; Water, for the forgiving; We've got a little bit of everything to represent and speak to all of the beautiful and unique souls that make our community great.  Take a load off and get yourself some home-brew at Burning Belgian Beer, where you can Feel the Sights and See the Sounds ~ lose your mind with the elements.

Events.Title: Regret, Relive, and Release
Events.Description: Is there something in your life that you wish could have went down differently? Maybe you would have liked to experience something with a loved one, but that person is now deceased. Possibly a bonding trip with an estranged sibling, your long-departed father getting to meet his grandchild, or an experience of baking cookies with a grandma you never knew. Use this opportunity to write a new narrative about an experience, and your relationship with the people who are no longer in your life. Take a regret, relive it in a new way, and release the pain.
